<subSubSection box="[151,1094,546,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1094,546,573]" box="[151,1094,546,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1094,546,573]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1094,546,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
Key to the subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Tsuneki, 1982" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1982" box="[457,699,546,573]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Thao">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[457,521,546,573]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Thao</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[527,699,546,572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="15 - 45" refId="ref3550" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1982) Studies on the new material of Sphecidae, Chrysididae and Mutillidae from Formosa and the Southern Ryukyus (Hymenoptera). Special Publications of the Japan Hymenopterists Association, 23, 15 - 45." type="journal article" year="1982">Tsuneki, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Leclercq, J." box="[903,1086,546,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref3269" refString="Leclercq, J. (1986) Crabroniens de Sri Lanka appartenent au genre Crossocerus Lepeletier &amp; Brulle, 1835 (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae). Bulletin &amp; Annales de la Societe Royale d'Entomologie de Belgique, 122, 243 - 252. [in French]" type="journal article" year="1986">Leclercq, 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
1. Light body parts white, not yellow; largely of this color: mandible, pronotal collar, pronotal lobe, scutellum, tegula; completely (without slightest darkened spot): scape, tibiae I-II; more than basal half of tibia III, large spots at apex of femora I-III, tarsi I-III (except apical tarsomeres brown). Trochanters completely amber yellow. Sterna light brown. Scutum punctures very sparse and fine but well defined, irregular. Pronotum collar perfectly rounded laterally. Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1150,704,726]" name="Brunei" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Brunei</collectingCountry>
.................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Leclercq 1986" authorityName="Leclercq" authorityYear="1986" box="[969,1436,733,755]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitidicorpus" subSpecies="uluanus">
<emphasis box="[969,1292,733,754]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Crossocerus nitidicorpus uluanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leclercq, J." box="[1298,1436,733,755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref3269" refString="Leclercq, J. (1986) Crabroniens de Sri Lanka appartenent au genre Crossocerus Lepeletier &amp; Brulle, 1835 (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae). Bulletin &amp; Annales de la Societe Royale d'Entomologie de Belgique, 122, 243 - 252. [in French]" type="journal article" year="1986">Leclercq 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" box="[151,1436,762,784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,762,784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">- Light body parts more or less pale yellow, not white. Tibiae I-II darkened on inner side............................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
2. Median lobe of clypeus quadridentate, medial tooth emarginate (Fig. 23 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[947,1081,792,814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref3592" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1984) Studies of the Philippine Crabroninae, revision and addition, with an annotated key to the species (Hymenoptera Sphecidae). Special Publications of the Japan Hymenopterists Association, 29, 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1984">Tsuneki 1984</bibRefCitation>
). Scutellum all black. Pronotal collar distinctly angulate laterally. Scutum punctation sparse and fine. Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1077,821,843]" name="Philippines" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Tsuneki 1984" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1984" box="[1026,1436,850,872]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitidicorpus" subSpecies="philippinicus">
<emphasis box="[1026,1301,850,872]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">C. nitidicorpus philippinicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[1307,1436,850,872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref3592" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1984) Studies of the Philippine Crabroninae, revision and addition, with an annotated key to the species (Hymenoptera Sphecidae). Special Publications of the Japan Hymenopterists Association, 29, 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1984">Tsuneki 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
- Median lobe of clypeus tridentate, medial tooth round or subtruncate apically. Scutellum broadly yellow or all black (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1421,880,902]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,184,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 9. Mesosoma, dorsal view; 10. Mesosoma, lateral view; 11. Propodeum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770976/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) ................................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
3. Pronotal collar broadly yellow upto to its side, which is slightly but visibly raised. Scutal punctures very sparse even at middle. Scape completely yellow; femora I-II with large yellow spot above apex; about basal half of tibia III yellow; metatarsus III all pale yellow; trochanters I-II amber yellow. Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[771,863,997,1019]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[871,924,997,1019]" country="Malaysia" name="Johor" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Johor</collectingRegion>
......... 
<taxonomicName authority="Leclercq 1986" authorityName="Leclercq" authorityYear="1986" box="[1043,1436,997,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitidicorpus" subSpecies="johorensis">
<emphasis box="[1043,1292,997,1018]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">C. nitidicorpus johorensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leclercq, J." box="[1298,1436,997,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref3269" refString="Leclercq, J. (1986) Crabroniens de Sri Lanka appartenent au genre Crossocerus Lepeletier &amp; Brulle, 1835 (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae). Bulletin &amp; Annales de la Societe Royale d'Entomologie de Belgique, 122, 243 - 252. [in French]" type="journal article" year="1986">Leclercq 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
- Pronotal collar perfectly rounded and not yellow laterally. Scutum relatively densely (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1106,1026,1048]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,184,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 9. Mesosoma, dorsal view; 10. Mesosoma, lateral view; 11. Propodeum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770976/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) punctate, especially at center and anteriorly (interspaces between punctures much larger than these). Scape more or less darkened dorsally toward apex; metatarsus III more or less largely darkened...................................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
4. Femora I-II largely yellow, with black spot beneath; trochanters I-III yellow apically; tibia III largely yellow. Clypeus: with well-rounded medial tooth, less prominent than lateral teeth (
<figureCitation box="[811,880,1143,1166]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,294,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-67@6.[151,1435,272,1739]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 12. Metasoma, lateral view; 13. Metasoma, dorsal view; 14. Metasoma, ventral view; 15. Pygidial plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770978/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[911,1040,1144,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref3505" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1968) Studies on the Formosan Sphecidae (V). The subfamily Crabroninae (Hymenoptera) with a key to the species of Crabronini occurring in Formosa and the Ryukyus. Etizenia, 30, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1968">Tsuneki 1968</bibRefCitation>
and Fig. 24 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[1186,1317,1144,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref3592" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1984) Studies of the Philippine Crabroninae, revision and addition, with an annotated key to the species (Hymenoptera Sphecidae). Special Publications of the Japan Hymenopterists Association, 29, 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1984">Tsuneki 1984</bibRefCitation>
, p. 13). Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[321,391,1173,1195]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Tsuneki, 1968" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1968" box="[1029,1436,1173,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitidicorpus" subSpecies="nitidicorpus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1295,1173,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">C. nitidicorpus nitidicorpus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[1301,1436,1173,1195]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref3505" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1968) Studies on the Formosan Sphecidae (V). The subfamily Crabroninae (Hymenoptera) with a key to the species of Crabronini occurring in Formosa and the Ryukyus. Etizenia, 30, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1968">Tsuneki, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" box="[151,1436,1202,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1202,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">- Femora I-II black, with small yellow spot at apex; other characters varying....................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
5. Yellow: all trochanters, basal 1/3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[541,553,1231,1243]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">rd</superScript>
of tibia III, scape except dorsal spot near apex; coxae of all legs, tergum I and sterna I-II all black; mandible yellow except apically. Clypeus: median carina absent, median tooth thick, almost truncate apically, lateral teeth slightly elongated. Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[591,687,1290,1312]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[697,785,1290,1312]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
.................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Leclercq, 1986" authorityName="Leclercq" authorityYear="1986" box="[1020,1436,1290,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitidicorpus" subSpecies="weddagalae">
<emphasis box="[1020,1286,1290,1312]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">C. nitidicorpus weddagalae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leclercq, J." box="[1292,1436,1290,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref3269" refString="Leclercq, J. (1986) Crabroniens de Sri Lanka appartenent au genre Crossocerus Lepeletier &amp; Brulle, 1835 (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae). Bulletin &amp; Annales de la Societe Royale d'Entomologie de Belgique, 122, 243 - 252. [in French]" type="journal article" year="1986">Leclercq, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
- Yellow: trochanter I with basal and apical spots, trochanter II except ventral spot, trochanter III completely, short dorsal stripe on tibia III basally, apical spot on coxae I-II, coxa III ventrally, scape except large dorsal stripe, tergum I basally, sternum I largely, patch on sternum II near base (
<figureCitation box="[599,684,1378,1400]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[194,1392,197,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[183,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Habitus, dorsal view; 3. Habitus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770968/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[715,742,1378,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,294,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-67@6.[151,1435,272,1739]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 12. Metasoma, lateral view; 13. Metasoma, dorsal view; 14. Metasoma, ventral view; 15. Pygidial plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770978/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">14</figureCitation>
); mandible ferruginous (
<figureCitation box="[979,1037,1378,1400]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,193,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head, lateral view; 6. Head, frontal view; 7. Antenna; 8. Clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770972/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Clypeus: medial carina present, median tooth of clypeus short and blunt, lateral teeth short (
<figureCitation box="[722,781,1408,1430]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,193,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head, lateral view; 6. Head, frontal view; 7. Antenna; 8. Clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770972/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[928,977,1408,1430]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">India</collectingCountry>
................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Saini &amp; Dey" authorityName="Saini &amp; Dey" box="[963,1313,1437,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Crossocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitidicorpus" subSpecies="indicus">
<emphasis box="[963,1182,1437,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">C. nitidicorpus indicus</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1189,1313,1437,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Saini &amp; Dey</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1313,1436,1437,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">, subsp. nov.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
